## Task Completion:

**1. Analyze and Describe the Main Target Image:**

- **Count & Layers:**
    - The structure is composed of **20 blocks**.
    - It has **4 layers**.
    - **Layer Breakdown (from bottom to top):**
        - Layer 1 (Base): 6 blocks (2 Yellow Squares, 2 Red Curved, 2 Orange Triangles)
        - Layer 2: 6 blocks (2 Green Rectangles, 2 Blue Squares, 2 Orange Squares)
        - Layer 3: 5 blocks (2 Blue Squares, 1 Green Rectangle, 2 Orange Triangles)
        - Layer 4 (Top): 3 blocks (2 Orange Triangles, 1 Orange Square)

- **Spatial Relationships:**
    - **Layer 1:** Two yellow square blocks form the base, placed side-by-side. Two red curved blocks are placed on top of the yellow squares, also side-by-side. Two orange triangular blocks are placed adjacent to the red curved blocks, forming a ramp-like base structure on the left side.
    - **Layer 2:** Two green rectangular blocks are placed on top of the yellow squares. Two blue square blocks are placed on top of the red curved blocks. Two orange square blocks are placed on top of the orange triangular blocks from layer 1.
    - **Layer 3:** Two blue square blocks are placed on top of the green rectangular blocks from layer 2. A green rectangular block is placed on top of the left orange square from layer 2. Two orange triangular blocks are placed on top of the orange squares from layer 2, next to the green rectangular block.
    - **Layer 4:** Two orange triangular blocks are placed on top of the blue square blocks from layer 3, forming the top corners. An orange square block is placed in the center, on top of the green rectangular block from layer 3.
